				<h2>Import your original API</h2>             
                <p>Your current API can use Azure App Service API application functions without changing any code. It uses ASP.NET, Java, PHP, Node.js or Python to create API apps. API apps can, along with mobile apps, use the same SDK and because of this you can effortlessly use your code on apps and the Web.</p>
                
				<h2>Enterprise level security</h2>
                <p>API Apps make protecting API easy. Protect your API apps with the help of Azure Active Directory (including client agent support from many third party services). It also provides rich support for WeChat and Weibo social networking authentication.</p>

                <h2>Simple access control</h2>
                <p>API Apps provides simple access control of API apps. Without changing code, you can open API to other apps within your organization and also open it to the public.</p>

                <h2>Automatic SDK generation</h2>
                <p>API Apps can use newly-acquired or currently-owned API and automatically generate SDK using a multitude of languages (including C#, Java, and JavaScript). This allows your enterprise to easily take API and use Web, mobile, or desktop apps.</p><br/><br/>
				
